<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-01-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-01-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="334" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Translation of telegrams from <gloss type="from">minister for foreign relations of Chile</gloss> to <gloss type="to">Chilean minister</gloss>, delivered to Mr.
                                    <persName>Blaine</persName> by Señor <persName>Montt</persName>,
                                January 15</hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-01-14"><hi rend="italic">January 14,
                                1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Minister <hi rend="smallcaps">Montt</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington:</hi></p>
                        <p>English Fireman Shields, of American merchant vessel <hi rend="italic">Keweenaw</hi>, was declared deserter by captain of vessel 24th
                            October last. Same day police took him up drunk in street.</p>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">January</hi> 11. Davidson accused of
                                stoning.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>